author: @ki6475
text: I love love loveee the vision of this album !!! He’s the only one who could pull off such visuals, imagery, sound and really reel you in effortlessly. 🤎 so glad he was able to work on so much of the album himself and enjoy the journey and those around him. All of the songs are something I can listen to, I’m not usually one for slow and dandy songs, but like I said, he’s the only one I could listen to pull it off because it feels more authentic to self and so I enjoy it more being able to know there’s actually real emotions and intention there 🌹it’s a real pleasure for me a listener to listen to the story behind certain songs and see the passion and drive to get it right from sound, tone, color, imagery, word play etc and keep it true to self as best as one can. When others are allowed the space like jaehyun to be themselves, the songs just hit different, feels more powerful and beautiful. It’s always a gift to receive the real someone, we need the real, the craft just becomes much more enjoyable and impactful. I personally never bought an album like ever…and so this just may be my first ever album I buy myself. Well done jaehyun, I’m rooting for you and the team.🥳 this journey is very inspiring.

text:
What more could i say? 

This man totally understood what he’s doing and delivered. 

For me, the moment i fell in love with Jaehyun is not because of his visual. The first time i saw Jaehyun among other NCT members, i was like “okay, he’s handsome. So what?” Until…listened to his voice. The moment i heard him sing, i was like “this is it! This is the kind of vocal i’ve been looking for in kpop or from a singer in general. His vocal is my kind of vocal and i love it so very much😭😭😭😭 he’s just so special. This album is just all about music and Jaehyun. And that what makes it so great. Good job, Jaehyun👏🏻 you’re the soloist of the year. J is the album of the year. Period.

author: @tenchfroast
text:
I'd suck at a tournament of favorites from the album because they switch depending on the timing and mood. My first listen, I hear all of the tracks once at random, and the ones that stand out immediately are my reflex tops. That was Can't Get You and Dandelion. All of the songs are wonderful, but I wasn't as excited about Roses yet. I also didn't know if I liked Completely because it's a good song or because I'm a romantic piano lover.

My second listen is to the album in order, earbuds, immersed. I found a new appreciation for Easy then, which was at the bottom on my first listen. I was neutral on Smoke but found myself singing it and loving it the more I did. Then I see which tracks I go back to most, which ones I play on repeat, which ones I skip. That's how I decide my treasures and guilty pleasures. Turns out, I skip nothing! I just play them in a different order to fit where my mind is at.

I enjoy FHL a lot now. I feel myself when I hear it because I look good in denim 😄I sink into Roses at night. Smoke feels essential without being weighed down by thought. I already decided to write my own tweaked version of Completely, not to change it but to express how I feel about it. Dandelion is still my joy. It makes me want to do cartwheels and make dumb faces.

But Can't Get You is my constant. From the first second of the first time to the last second of every time since, I'm in love with it. I disappear in it. I close my eyes and dance to it. It's not only the best song on the album. It's a fantastic song in general, and I think people can appreciate how good it is even if it's not their style.

tldr; Jae didn't disappoint. This first album is a success as a journey into J and as a musical vibe. I really hope more people get to hear and support it! ❤

text: This evening, I listened to the album with the intention of choosing my favorite song. I was almost certain it would be "Roses" because of its impact—it’s such a hit. Or maybe "Completely," simply because it makes me cry, and to me, that means it’s good. But then "Dandelion" started playing, and I found myself thinking, has it always sounded like this? It felt so different, listening to it as part of the whole album. For me, the other songs highlight what I love most about "Dandelion," making it truly shine. This song genuinely feels like Jaehyun is smiling. It’s just his smile captured in a song. It's the one I love and cherish the most—my favorite. Thank you for this gift, uri J<33333333

text:
내가 재현이를 보면서 느낀 건 재현이는 모든 일에 있어서 내가 더 인정받고 사랑받으려면 나부터 잘해야 돼 내가 더욱더 노력해야 돼 라는 마음가짐으로 항상 최선을 다한다는 거야 얼마나 기특해… 재현이가 이번 솔로 앨범이 처음인 만큼 더 좋은 모습을 보여주고 싶어서 많은 노력을 기울였다는 건 알고 있었지만 다큐 보는데 아… 내가 생각했던 거 보다 훨씬 더 많은 노력을 했구나 많이 힘들었겠구나 싶었어 항상 밝은 모습만 보여주려고 하고 과정보다 결과를 보여주려고 했던 재현이를 생각하면
마음이 너무 아픈데 그와 동시에 그런 어려움 속에서도 포기하지 않고 최선을 다해줘서 고맙고 너무 자랑스러운 거 같아 재현이의 진심과 노력이 결국엔 더 큰 결실을 맺을 거고 준비하면서 재현이를 힘들게 했던 어려움들은 결국에 너를 더 빛나고 강하게 만들어 주는 계기가 될 거라고 생각해 재현이를 보면 영원히 응원하고 싶다는 생각이 들어 너무 자랑스럽고 고마워!! 재현이 정말 고생 많았고 앞으로도 네가 걸어가는 길에 항상 함께하며 응원할게 많이 사랑해

text: 진짜 고민 많이 했구나 재현이.. 🥺재현아 모두가 듣기에 호불호 없고 대중적이지 않더라도 꼭 그게 정답은 아니라고 생각하고 재현이가 가지고 있는 장르,색깔이 너무 색다르고 새로워서 좋았고 재현이를 있는 그대로 보여준 거 같아서 너무 좋았어 재현이가 제일 잘 하고 제일 좋아하는 걸 담는 게 난 맞다고 생각하고 사람들이 선호하는 걸 하려고 그거에 맞추는 것보단 지금 재현이가 낸 곡들이 정말 시간이 지나도 오래도록 질리지 않고 들을 수 있는 매력적인 좋은 곡들이라고 생각해 그리고 이런 장르를 이렇게 잘 소화해낼 수 있는 가수도 그동안 우리나라에 없었다고 생각하거든? 그래서 정말 뻔하지 않아서 너무 좋았어 클래식 고전영화 옛날부터 꾸준히 인기 있는 해외 알앤비 팝송 그런 것들은 언제든 다시 꺼내봐도 좋잖아 난 재현이가 클래식이랑 너무 잘 어울리는 사람이라고 생각해 재현이 진짜 너무 잘했고 노래 너무 좋고 수고했어💚
